{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a568145-1037-48af-a008-04485581222c","content":"In .NET MAUI, the `Application` class no longer has `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` overrides. Instead, use the **`Window` lifecycle events**:\n\n```csharp\npublic partial class App : Application\n{\n    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    {\n        var window = new Window(new AppShell());\n\n        window.Created += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnStart */ };\n        window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnSleep */ };\n        window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnResume */ };\n\n        return window;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Lifecycle is now **per-window**, supporting multi-window scenarios.\n- Additional events are available: `Activated`, `Deactivated`, `Destroying`, `Backgrounding`.\n- For platform-specific hooks, you can also use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4dd55286-90c6-4621-9e73-1a28e10736a2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI, specifically about the Application lifecycle methods (OnStart, OnSleep, OnResume). This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":314,"requestId":"1438:2950B:69B40F2:720CE21:6A03CCDC"},"id":"73f33523-ec75-4ca7-9210-36a2c2ff80bf","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:59:16.210Z","parentId":"fe8eed0a-1748-4b18-b0ad-6e7b47bc5a5c"}
